If you run a hedge fund, and then you leave the hedge fund and sign a non-c=
ompete agreement, and then you get into the business of managing money for =
one of the hedge fund=E2=80=99s top clients, that=E2=80=99s =E2=80=A6=C2=A0=
weird isn=E2=80=99t it? Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Ben Bartenstein reports:An inve=
stment partnership between Ray Dalio=E2=80=99s family office and Abu Dhabi =
royal Sheikh Tahnoon bin Zayed Al Nahyan has been delayed as Bridgewater As=
sociates grapples with the legal terms of its billionaire founder=E2=80=99s=
 exit from the firm. =E2=80=A6The 74-year-old signed a non-compete agreemen=
t upon departing the world=E2=80=99s largest hedge fund several years ago, =
the people said, requesting anonymity as the matter is private. Dalio=E2=80=
=99s planned venture with Sheikh Tahnoon, one of Bridgewater=E2=80=99s top =
