</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are a trader, a good skill to h=
ave is buying stuff that will go up. If the stuff =E2=80=94=C2=A0stocks, bo=
nds, currencies, whatever =E2=80=94 that you buy reliably goes up, then you=
 can make a lot of money. You can make money simply by buying the stuff, ha=
ving it go up, and then selling it for more money than you paid. But there =
are other ways to monetize the skill. You can start an investment newslette=
r, and charge people a fee for telling them what stuff will go up. You can =
start a hedge fund, buying stuff for other people and taking a cut of their=
 profits.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile, other people might try=
 to free-ride on your skill. People might find out what you are buying =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0your broker will see your orders, or maybe you=E2=80=99re runni=
ng a hedge fund and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/clic=
k/36145613.193392/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwM=
jQtMDUtMTUvaGVkZ2UtZnVuZHMtcHVtcC11cC1leHBvc3VyZS10by1udmlkaWEtY3V0LWFtZC0x=
M2Ytd3JhcD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNzIyMjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9=
zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA3MjImdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1Zm=
Y/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB20675d0b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"it=
emscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !=
important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-b=
ottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">have to disclose</a> what you =
buy<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: tr=
ansparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a> =E2=80=94=C2=A0and might try to copy you, since what you buy keeps goi=
ng up. Your purchases=C2=A0<em>contain information </em>=E2=80=94=C2=A0they=
 encode the message =E2=80=9Cthis stuff will probably go up=E2=80=9D =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0and that information is valuable.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
If you are a trader, another =E2=80=A6=C2=A0skill? =E2=80=A6=C2=A0you might=
 have is buying stuff that will go=C2=A0<em>down</em>. You keep saying =E2=
=80=9Cooh this stock is poised to go to the moon,=E2=80=9D you buy it, it g=
oes to zero. This skill seems somehow more attainable than the first skill,=
=C2=A0though it=E2=80=99s not clear that that=E2=80=99s actually true.<a cl=
ass=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparen=
t !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a> It is harder to make money with this skill. If you buy stuff, and it g=
oes down, and you sell it, you will have <em>less=C2=A0</em>money.</p><p st=
yle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Oh, I know, I know, you can try <a href=3D"https://=
link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/36145613.193392/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cueW91d=
HViZS5jb20vd2F0Y2g_dj1DaXp3SF9UN3BqZw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5b917c86" it=
emprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #=
ccc;">the George Costanza approach</a>: Any time you think you should buy a=
 stock, you sell it instead. But this seems tricky to do yourself; it requi=
res not only the self-knowledge to say =E2=80=9CI keep getting things wrong=
=E2=80=9D but also the ability to continually analyze your instincts to ide=
ntify the valuable=C2=A0signal. =E2=80=9CAfter extensive research and analy=
sis, I want to buy this stock, which means I should sell it,=E2=80=9D you t=
hink, but what if actually <em>that </em>is the=C2=A0impulse you should be =
resisting? How do you know where to stop your conscious analysis and do the=
 opposite of the result?<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important;=
 background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a></p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Can you monetize the skill in other wa=
ys? I think if you have a strong track record and a rigorous repeatable pro=
cess of only buying stocks that go down, you really=C2=A0<em>should=C2=A0</=
em>be able to start a newsletter or get hired by a hedge fund to tell peopl=
e your best ideas (so they can short them), but again I think this is trick=
y in practice. Probably if you waltz in the door at Citadel and are like =
=E2=80=9Chi my superpower is that I am exceptionally terrible at picking st=
ocks=E2=80=9D they will have doubts. I bet there=E2=80=99s some sell-side e=
quity research analyst out there who is kept on the payroll for making reli=
ably wrong stock picks, but it can=E2=80=99t be that common.</p><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">Can other people free-ride on your skill? Can they look a=
t your track record and say =E2=80=9Ceverything this person picks goes down=
, so I should short it=E2=80=9D? I mean! Tuttle Capital Management once lau=
nched some very rude exchange-traded funds to fade <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/36145613.193392/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZX=
JnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMDIvc2lsdmVyZ2F0ZS1oYWQtYS1jcnlwd=
G8tYmFuay1ydW4_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDcyMjI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1=
dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwNzIyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN=
0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb8f8aabe" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Jim Cramer=E2=80=99s</a>=
 and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/36145613.1933=
92/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDQtMTgvY3Jl=
YXRvci1vZi1hbnRpLWFyay1ldGYtbWF0dC10dXR0bGUtbG9va3MtdG8tcmVwZWF0LXRyaWNrLWF=
mdGVyLWxvc2luZy1mdW5kP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA3MjIyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW=
1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDcyMiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249b=
W9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4da64aa5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" ite=
mscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Cathie Wood=E2=80=
=99s</a>=C2=A0stock picks, but I don=E2=80=99t think those had <a href=3D"h=
ttps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/36145613.193392/aHR0cHM6Ly9maW=
5hbmNlLnlhaG9vLmNvbS9uZXdzL2ludmVyc2UtamltLWNyYW1lci1ldGYtc2h1dHRlcmVkLTE0M=
