a>; it is not actually the case that Cramer or Wood has this sort of anti-s=
kill. In general, if your stock picks are <em>known=C2=A0</em>broadly, they=
=E2=80=99re probably not bad enough to make betting against you a reliable =
strategy.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand,=C2=A0your=C2=
=A0<em>broker=C2=A0</em>probably knows (1) what you=E2=80=99re buying and (=
2) how you=E2=80=99re doing. If you=E2=80=99re terrible, your broker might =
be tempted.=C2=A0Here is a funny <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/36145613.193392/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY21lZ3JvdXAuY29tL25vdGljZXMv=
