1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">Bloomberg Businessweek article</a> about a Harvard Business Sc=
hool marketing professor who, unsurprisingly, is very good at this:</p><blo=
ckquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anita Elberse =E2=80=A6=C2=A0is best k=
nown for her course The Business of Entertainment, Media, and Sports=E2=80=
=94or #BEMS to its alumni who post about it on Instagram and LinkedIn. The =
four-day, $12,000 program, an elective open to professionals not enrolled a=
t HBS, has become a blockbuster for the university. Elberse=E2=80=99s case =
studies, ranging from=C2=A0David Beckham=E2=80=99s brand management to=C2=
=A0Beyonc=C3=A9=E2=80=99s music launch strategies, are often announced like=
 an album drop on social media. Which is why, along with execs from Hollywo=
od and Madison Avenue, stars such as=C2=A0Channing Tatum=C2=A0and=C2=A0LL C=
ool J=C2=A0have signed up, hoping to build the next celebrity business empi=
re.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Its appeal isn=E2=80=99t just that it a=
llows C-level normies to study alongside celebrities but also that it allow=
s famous people to feel like Ivy Leaguers. =E2=80=9CThis week I got accepte=
d into Harvard! Words cannot describe my excitement!=E2=80=9D posted singer=
 Ciara online after getting into Elberse=E2=80=99s program in 2019. =E2=80=
=9CCourse complete!=E2=80=9D declared Fixer Upper moguls Chip and Joanna Ga=
ines on Instagram the same year, next to a photo of the couple wearing Harv=
ard letter sweaters and holding up diplomas. (Elberse later wrote a case on=
 their Magnolia Network.) =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This ye=
ar marks the program=E2=80=99s 10th anniversary. Elberse says the more it g=
rows in popularity, the more she has to guard against celebs co-opting the =
Harvard brand to further their own. =E2=80=9CWe sometimes say =E2=80=98no=
=E2=80=99 to people if I don=E2=80=99t get a sense they=E2=80=99re here for=
 the right reasons,=E2=80=9D she says. =E2=80=9CThis is not about you takin=
g photos walking around the Harvard campus.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p sty=
le=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I mean, it is a little bit, right? Like if you have =
a lot of Instagram followers and you post yourself in a Harvard sweater wal=
king around the campus, that is just good for everyone=E2=80=99s business.<=
